h1. YAML Selector

The YAML Selector makes it easy to get data (variables) from YAML files.
Use PHP to select a deep nested strings in a YAML file. It also supports variable replacements.

See/run the index.php file for more information about it's usage, but in short:

bc. require_once("yaml_selector.php");
$yaml = new YamlSelector("example_file.yaml");
$yaml->get("keyname");
$yaml->get("firstlevel.secondlevel");

For more examples, like the replacement function, see the index.php file.